    <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl">Failing Forward</h1> 
    <p class="mt-6 text-xl leading-8">Hi, I'm Dillon. I'm the artist behind the pieces here, and the developer who built this website.</p>
    <div class="mt-10 max-w-2xl">
      <p>The story of this site starts when El Salvador made Bitcoin legal tender. I had just gotten a remote engineering job to be a
       digital nomad for a while. When El Salvador made the announcement, I canceled my airbnb's, changed my flight and moved there to 
       see what was going on. I learned some important things</p>
      <ul role="list" class="mt-8 max-w-xl space-y-8 text-gray-600">
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <svg class="mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-indigo-600" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.857-9.809a.75.75 0 00-1.214-.882l-3.483 4.79-1.88-1.88a.75.75 0 10-1.06 1.061l2.5 2.5a.75.75 0 001.137-.089l4-5.5z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
          <span><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Bitcoin Is Important For Humanity</strong> There's so many things wrong with out banking system. Things like inflation, digital tracking and the government deciding what you can spen your money on are a few examples.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <svg class="mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-indigo-600" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.857-9.809a.75.75 0 00-1.214-.882l-3.483 4.79-1.88-1.88a.75.75 0 10-1.06 1.061l2.5 2.5a.75.75 0 001.137-.089l4-5.5z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
          <span><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Programable Money Is Awesome For Business</strong> Things like automatic profit sharing, dynamic investments, automatic supply purchasing based on triggers are some of the many applications that businesses and entrepreneurs have yet to innovate with. There is so much oportunity in the way of programmable money.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-x-3">
          <svg class="mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-indigo-600" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.857-9.809a.75.75 0 00-1.214-.882l-3.483 4.79-1.88-1.88a.75.75 0 10-1.06 1.061l2.5 2.5a.75.75 0 001.137-.089l4-5.5z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
          <span><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900">It's only digital money.</strong>It's really hard buy things in the real world with it. 
          Many of the vendors in El Salvador complained about this. If they accepted Bitcoin, they would need to sell it for cash at an ATM for a 5% fee, and that's assuming it doesn't go down. 
          A 5% fee in a 3rd world country is a lot.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-8">So these are some interesting things. And I'm not just curious, I like to build and invent things</p>
      <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">So I decided to sell coffee</h2>
      <p class="mt-6">While I was pretending to work at my remote job, I was hustling in the coffee business. Mostly as a proof of concept. Trying to see what the business model would look like for a crypto for CPG company would look like. </p>
      <figure class="mt-10 border-l border-indigo-600 pl-9">
        <blockquote class="font-semibold text-gray-900">
          <p>Because how will crypto make us free when you have to stay glued to a screen?</p>
        </blockquote>
      </figure>
      <p class="mt-10">The real world is where it matters. But, the time I chose to do this was the worst time possible. Shipping rates were insane, thanks to covid. Recurring payments were impossible, and I lost my job. </P>
      <p class="mt-10">My manager got wise to what I was doing, and my performance was slacking. I was fired. I ran out of money and couldn't pay for any business expense. I moved to Austin Tx to persue this coffee business. But lost my 
      income around 5 months after I moved there.
    
      </p>
    </div>
    

